# EVOLUTION.log — Invincible.Inc
A ledger of major architectural transitions and strategic milestones.

[2026-03-29] 💎 C-LEVEL MATRIX PIVOT (Nuitka)
- **Hardening:** Abandoned PyInstaller (script zipping) for Nuitka (C-compilation). 
- **Anti-Reverse Engineering:** Source code is now translated to C and compiled to machine code, making .pyc unpacking impossible.
- **Bypass:** Resolved Windows SmartScreen/LoadLibrary failures by eliminating the temporary extraction folder dependency.
- **Performance:** Native memory management for high-speed SIGINT processing.
- **Orchestration:** Transitioned from raw Python scripts to a Windows-distributable architecture.
- **UI Architecture:** Engineered the Lattice SIGINT COP (LatticeSignalView.jsx) to handle high-speed ingestion (500ms bursts).
- **Security:** Implemented zero-redirect download logic on the Explainer website to maintain operator presence.
- **Packaging:** Created the Inno Setup blueprint (Invincible_Setup.iss) with custom EULA and AppData installation support.
- **Ingestion:** Deployed the HighSpeedCaptureEngine (Signal_Ingestion_Module.py) to replace sequential scanning with a ring-buffer model.
- **Critical Fix:** Shifted to **Single-Binary (--onefile)** architecture to resolve "Missing Python312.dll" errors on non-dev machines. All dependencies are now statically bundled.

[2026-03-28] 🏗️ FOUNDATION PHASE
- Established the standardized agent fleet (Claude, Gemini, Codex, OpenCode).
- Unified the project registry in .ai-agents/manifest.md.
- Developed the core SIGINT/DeFlock mapping backend.
